title: S2 Ep1: Are there too many farms in the world?
itunes:title: Are there too many farms in the world?
description: Low-income countries have many small farms, and high-income countries have far fewer large farms and much higher agricultural productivity. Tim Phillips asks Mark Rosenzweig whether developing countries would be better off with bigger farms.
